==Further reading== *[https://obamawhitehouse.archives.gov/sites/default/files/docs/one_today_inaugural_poem_by_richard_blanco_jan._21_2013.pdf ''One Today'' at White House website] *{{cite web |url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/today-richard-blanco-poem-read-barack-obama-inauguration/story?id=18274653 |title=''One Today'': Full Text of Richard Blanco Inaugural Poem |last=Bruce |first=Mary |publisher=ABC News |date=January 21, 2013}} Includes a video of Blanco's reading. *{{cite web |url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2013/01/21/richard-blanco-obama-s-historic-inauguration-poet.html |title=Richard Blanco, Obama’s Historic Inauguration Poet |work=[[The Daily Beast]] |last=Freedlander |first=David |date=January 21, 2013}} Freedlander summarizes several opinions about Blanco's poem, as well as giving the poem's text. *{{cite web |url=http://blogs.loc.gov/catbird/2013/01/richard-blancos-inaugural-poem-one-today/ |title=Richard Blanco's Inaugural Poem: ''One Today'' |last=Armenti |first=Peter |date=January 28, 2013 |work=From the Catbird Seat: Poetry & Literature at the Library of Congress}} Armenti offers a careful explication of the poem, stanza by stanza.
